note.p: NLS Adv. 72.1.2 is a large and diverse manuscript associated with the Beaton family. While it contains a large number of medical texts, other fields of learning, such as logic and cosmology, are also well-represented. Furthermore, some of the medical items are unusual, compared to what is available from other manuscripts. A selection of of texts from the manuscript is presented here, with material on otherwise poorly represented subjects being given priority.

note.p: This 'commórtas' has been tentatively identified as being in the hand of the Rev. John Beaton (Hand16). The ink is similar to that used by the latter on fol. 92v of the present manuscript and he adds marginal notes elsewhere in NLS Adv. 72.1.2. The hand is not particularly similar (although compare "d" here and on fol. 92v) and could be trying to impersonate that of Eoin mac Domhnaill Ó Conchubhair (Hand20), above.
